# Figma Extractify — Next.js 16 + Tailwind CSS v4

This is Figma Extractify. Components are built in isolation, previewed locally, and exported as typed, props-driven React modules. This is NOT a full Next.js application — routes under `src/app/` are preview pages only.

## Before writing any code

Read `_docs/SKILL.md` for the step-by-step workflow, then:
- `_docs/start-here.md` — golden rules
- `_docs/structure/project-rules.md` — naming and file conventions
- `_docs/learnings.md` — top 10 common mistakes

## Golden rules

- Never use a bare `<img>` — always `<Image>` from `next/image`
- Never wrap `<Image>` in `<figure>` unless a `<figcaption>` is present (`next/image` handles `<picture>` internally)
- Use `<Link>` from `next/link` only for internal Next.js routes; use plain `<a>` for `mailto:`, `tel:`, and external URLs
- No CSS modules — use Tailwind utilities or PostCSS under `src/assets/css/`
- All components are fully props-driven — no hardcoded content, no internal data fetching
- All values in rem, never px (1rem = 16px)
- Every new component needs a preview page at `src/app/components/<name>/page.tsx` and a link in `src/app/page.tsx`

## Tech stack

- Next.js 16 (App Router, Turbopack)
- React 19
- Tailwind CSS v4 (CSS-first config via `@theme` in PostCSS)
- TypeScript strict mode

## Key paths

- Components: `src/components/<ComponentName>/index.tsx`
- Preview routes: `src/app/components/<name>/page.tsx`
- Design tokens: `src/assets/css/base/theme.pcss`
- Typography utilities: `src/assets/css/base/typography.pcss`
- Button utilities: `src/assets/css/base/buttons.pcss`
- Figma URL registry: `_docs/figma-paths.yaml`
